{"lemma": "زادٌ", "slug": "زادٌ", "root": "ز.#.د", "root_slug": "ز-_-د", "root_link": "/words/roots/ز-_-د", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "زاد", "root": "زود", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n18369", "n18485", "n18372"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "provisions", "fa": "توشه", "ur": "خوراک", "tr": "yol gıdası", "id": "bekal", "bn": "খাদ্য", "es": "provisiones", "fr": "provisions", "de": "Verpflegung", "ru": "припасы", "zh": "干粮"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to add"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to increase"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to supply, provide"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/zaː.da/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n18369", "headword_ar": "زَادَ", "root": "zwd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yazuwdu", "text_ar": "يَزُودُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (L,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zawodN", "text_ar": "زَوْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (L, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He laid in a stock of provisions for travelling"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for a fixed residence;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^as~asa zaAdFA", "text_ar": "اَسَّسَ زَادًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (L, K:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAdahu", "text_ar": "زَادَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaw~adahu", "text_ar": "زَوَّدَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; q. v.; and this is what is meant in the K by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taA^osiysu Alz~aAdi", "text_ar": "تَاْسِيسُ الزَّادِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as the explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alz~awodu", "text_ar": "الزَّوْدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (MF.)"}], "source_refs": ["L", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n18485", "headword_ar": "زَادَ", "root": "zyd", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaziydu", "text_ar": "يَزِيدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdapN", "text_ar": "زِيَادَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, * Msb, K *) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodN", "text_ar": "زَيْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, *) with which are syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziydN", "text_ar": "زِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayadN", "text_ar": "زَيَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maziydN", "text_ar": "مَزِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zayodaAnN", "text_ar": "زَيْدَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which last is anomalous, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$anoA=nN", "text_ar": "شَنْا=نٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lay~aAnN", "text_ar": "لَيَّانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said to be the only instances of the kind, (TA,) all as inf. ns., (TK,) and so is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mazaAdN", "text_ar": "مَزَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) and J adds that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zuwaAdapN", "text_ar": "زُوَادَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is mentioned by Yaakoob, from Ks, from El-Bekree, as syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdapN", "text_ar": "زِيَادَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but this is a mistake, which is unfairly imputed to J by the author of the K, (MF,) [who says,] as to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alz~uwaAdapu", "text_ar": "الزُّوَادَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", it is a mistranscription by J, for the words are"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alz~uwaArapu", "text_ar": "الزُّوَارَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alz~iyaArapu", "text_ar": "الزِّيَارَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~uwAdpu", "text_ar": "الرُّوادةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~iyAdpu", "text_ar": "الرِّيادةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "r", "text_ar": "ر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and without the mention of [the signification of]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~umuw~u", "text_ar": "النُّمُوُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a thing, S, Mgh, Msb, [as, for ex.,] water, and property, A)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "increased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "augmented,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grew;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, TA;) [and in like manner said of a man, and of any animal;] as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AizodaAda", "text_ar": "اِزْدَادَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K:) or this latter has a more intensive signification than the former, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aikotasaba", "text_ar": "اِكْتَسَبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in relation to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kasaba", "text_ar": "كَسَبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (MF. [See also 5.]) In this sense it has a single objective complement; as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAda ka*aA", "text_ar": "زَادَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he, increased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "augmented,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "grew, in such a thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AizodaAda", "text_ar": "اِزْدَادَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [The latter is more commonly used in this manner.] You say, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aizodadotu", "text_ar": "اِزْدَدْتُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAlFA", "text_ar": "مَالًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh, Msb) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I increased in property:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also] meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I increased to myself,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for myself, property."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, * Msb.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^amoru", "text_ar": "الاَمْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AzdAd", "text_ar": "ازداد", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuEuwbapF", "text_ar": "صُعُوبَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The affair increased in difficulty"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b2-  [Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It exceeded; it was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, redundant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "superfluous; it remained over and above."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAda Ealayohi", "text_ar": "زَادَ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It exceeded it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tzAyd", "text_ar": "تزايد", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAda EalaY Al$~aYo'i DiEofahu", "text_ar": "زَادَ عَلَى الشَّىْءِ ضِعْفَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It exceeded the thing by the like thereof,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "more"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAda EalaY maA A^araAda", "text_ar": "زَادَ عَلَى مَا اَرَادَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It exceeded what he desired"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A.) ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He gave an addition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the  saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faqado A^arobaY", "text_ar": "فَقَدْ اَرْبَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano zaAda waA@zodaAda", "text_ar": "مَنْ زَادَ وَا@زْدَادَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He who gives an addition, and who takes it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[each of these]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "practises usury."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b4-  [And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He added,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "exaggerated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaziydu fiY Hadiyvihi", "text_ar": "يَزِيدُ فِى حَدِيثِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He adds,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "exaggerates, in his narration,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "talk,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "discourse,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is said of a liar. (A and TA voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sar~aAjN", "text_ar": "سَرَّاجٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [See also 5.])       -A2-  It is also trans.: (Msb:) you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAdahu", "text_ar": "زَادَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaziyduhu", "text_ar": "يَزِيدُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ziyaAdapN", "text_ar": "زِيَادَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He increased it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "augmented it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L.) And in this sense it is doubly trans.: (MF:) you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAdahu A@ll~`hu xayorFA", "text_ar": "زَادَهُ ا@للّٰهُ خَيْرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maAlFA", "text_ar": "مَالًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God increased to him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "added to him, good fortune"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "prosperity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "property; increased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "added to, his good fortune,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may God increase"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.;] as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zay~adahu", "text_ar": "زَيَّدَهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAda fiymaA Einodahu", "text_ar": "زَادَ فِيمَا عِنْدَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY maAlihi", "text_ar": "فِى مَالِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He increased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "added to, what he possessed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his possessions,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his property;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "may He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(i. e. God)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "increase"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.] ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zaAdahu", "text_ar": "زَادَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He gave him an increase,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an addition,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "more."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) See 10. ―         -b3-  You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaziyduka A^aHadN Ealayohi", "text_ar": "يَزِيدُكَ اَحَدٌ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "No one is more sufficient for thee than he"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "znd", "text_ar": "زند"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". [See 4 in that art.]) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA yaziyduka Ealayohi jamalN", "text_ar": "لَا يَزِيدُكَ عَلَيْهِ جَمَلٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "No camel will be more sufficient for thee than he; i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA yaDur~uka", "text_ar": "لَا يَضُرُّكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (ISk, S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Dr", "text_ar": "ضر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in which see other exs.].)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "A", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "TA", "TK", "MF"]}, {"entry_id": "n18372", "headword_ar": "زَادٌ", "root": "zwd", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Provisions,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a stock of provisions, for travelling"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L, Msb, TA) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for a fixed residence:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^azowaAdN", "text_ar": "اَزْوَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^azowidapN", "text_ar": "اَزْوِدَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the latter anomalous. (L.) ―         -b2-  And hence, as being likened thereto, (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Any deed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "acquirement,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "whether"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "evil, whereby one becomes changed in state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L;) [or rather,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whereby one provides for a change of state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition, like as a traveller provides for a journey."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] It is"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1268}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said in the Kur [ii. 193],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA_in~a xayora Alz~aAdi", "text_ar": "فَاـِنَّ خَيْرَ الزَّادِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "watazaw~aduwA", "text_ar": "وَتَزَوَّدُوا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aqowaY", "text_ar": "التَّقْوَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L) meaning, [as is implied in the L, (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And make ye provision; but verily the best acquirement whereby to provide for a change of state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition, is fear"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of God, or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piety:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the meaning is]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and prepare ye provisions for your journey; and verily the best provision is that whereby one provides against begging from others, &c."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Jel.) ―         -b3-  [It is also said to be used as meaning (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Salutation and the returning of a greeting."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., ii. 415, q. v.)]"}], "source_refs": ["S", "L", "Msb", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF/", "headword_ar": "زاد", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_31", "lexicon_en": "Al-Rāghib al-Isfahānī, al-Mufradāt fī Gharīb al-Qurʾān (d. c. 1109 CE)", "lexicon_ar": "المفردات في غريب القرآن للراغب الأصفهاني", "permalink": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=61770#2dc01c", "body_html": "<span class=\"title1\">زاد</span><br><span>الزِّيادَةُ: أن ينضمّ إلى ما عليه الشيء في نفسه شيء آخر، يقال: زِدْتُهُ فَازْدَادَ، وقوله وَنَزْدادُ كَيْلَ بَعِيرٍ [يوسف/ 65] ، نحو: ازْدَدْتُ فضلا، أي: ازداد فضلي، وهو من باب: سَفِهَ نَفْسَهُ [البقرة/ 130] ، وذلك قد يكون زيادة مذمومة كالزّيادة على الكفاية، مثل زيادة الأصابع، والزّوائد في قوائم الدّابّة، وزِيَادَةُ الكبد، وهي قطعة معلّقة بها يتصوّر أن لا حاجة إليها لكونها غير مأكولة، وقد تكون زيادة محمودة، نحو قوله: لِلَّذِينَ أَحْسَنُوا الْحُسْنى وَزِيادَةٌ</span><br><span>[يونس/ 26] ، وروي من طرق مختلفة أنّ هذه الزّيادة النّظر إلى وجه الله ، إشارة إلى إنعام وأحوال لا يمكن تصوّرها في الدّنيا.</span><br><span>وَزادَهُ بَسْطَةً فِي الْعِلْمِ وَالْجِسْمِ</span><br><span>[البقرة/ 247] ، أي: أعطاه من العلم والجسم قدرا يزيد على ما أعطى أهل زمانه، وقوله: وَيَزِيدُ اللَّهُ الَّذِينَ اهْتَدَوْا هُدىً</span><br><span>[مريم/ 76] ، ومن الزّيادة المكروهة قوله: ما زادَهُمْ إِلَّا نُفُوراً</span><br><span>[فاطر/ 42] ، وقوله: زِدْناهُمْ عَذاباً فَوْقَ الْعَذابِ [النحل/ 88] ، فَما تَزِيدُونَنِي غَيْرَ تَخْسِيرٍ [هود/ 63] ، وقوله: فَزادَهُمُ اللَّهُ مَرَضاً [البقرة/ 10] ، فإنّ هذه الزّيادة هو ما بني عليه جبلّة الإنسان، أنّ من تعاطى فعلا إن خيرا وإن شرّا تقوّى فيما يتعاطاه فيزداد حالا فحالا. وقوله:</span><br><span>هَلْ مِنْ مَزِيدٍ</span><br><span>[ق/ 30] ، يجوز أن يكون ذلك استدعاء للزّيادة، ويجوز أن يكون تنبيها أنها قد امتلأت، وحصل فيها ما ذكر تعالى في قوله:</span><br><span>لَأَمْلَأَنَّ جَهَنَّمَ مِنَ الْجِنَّةِ وَالنَّاسِ [السجدة/ 13] . يقال: زدته، وزاد هو، وازْدَادَ، قال وَازْدَادُوا تِسْعاً [الكهف/ 25] ، وقال: ثُمَّ ازْدادُوا كُفْراً [آل عمران/ 90] ، وَما تَغِيضُ الْأَرْحامُ وَما تَزْدادُ [الرعد/ 8] ، وشرّ زَائِدٌ وزَيْدٌ. قال الشاعر:</span><br><span>وأنتمو معشر زيد على مائة فأجمعوا أمركم كيدا فكيدوني</span><br><span>والزَّادُ: المدّخر الزّائد على ما يحتاج إليه في الوقت، والتَّزَوُّدُ: أخذ الزّاد، قال: وَتَزَوَّدُوا فَإِنَّ خَيْرَ الزَّادِ التَّقْوى</span><br><span>[البقرة/ 197] ، والْمِزْوَدُ: ما يجعل فيه الزّاد من الطّعام، والْمَزَادَةُ: ما يجعل فيه الزّاد من الماء.</span>"}]}, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}